# Day 112: Connecting Spring Boot to Redis

**Topics Covered:**
1. Adding `spring-boot-starter-data-redis`.
2. Configuring host and port in `application.yml`.
3. The `RedisTemplate` class.
4. CRUD operations on Redis manually.

**Learning Summary:**
Today I connected my app to Redis. I used `RedisTemplate` to save and retrieve data manually. It works just like a `HashMap` but runs on a server.
- `opsForValue().set(key, value)` -> Save data.
- `opsForValue().get(key)` -> Get data.

**Code Snippet:**
```java
@Configuration
public class RedisConfig {
    @Bean
    public RedisTemplate<String, Object> redisTemplate(RedisConnectionFactory connectionFactory) {
        RedisTemplate<String, Object> template = new RedisTemplate<>();
        template.setConnectionFactory(connectionFactory);
        return template;
    }
}

// Usage
redisTemplate.opsForValue().set("user:1", new User("Amit", "Dev"));
User u = (User) redisTemplate.opsForValue().get("user:1");
